[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm sure this has come up before, but here goes.<br>\nWhat would this mean?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>&lt;name&gt;\n    &lt;use value=&quot;official&quot;/&gt;\n&lt;/name&gt;\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Am I asserting that I do not know the official name?<br>\nIs it a piece of nonsense?</p>",
        "id": 153903165,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How about?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>&lt;name/&gt;\n</pre></div>",
        "id": 153903166,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When would HumanName be used with no name content?</p>",
        "id": 153903167,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, communicating nothing about a name says nothing about a name. In this case if you really wanted to explicitly communicate that you do not know the name, use the <a href=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/extension-data-absent-reason.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.hl7.org/fhir/extension-data-absent-reason.html\">https://www.hl7.org/fhir/extension-data-absent-reason.html</a> extension instead.</p>",
        "id": 153903168,
        "sender_full_name": "Ewout Kramer",
        "timestamp": 1503387187
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fair enough.</p>",
        "id": 153903169,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387237
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So <code>&lt;name/&gt;</code> actually says nothing about name.<br>\n<img alt=\":simple_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"/static/generated/emoji/images/emoji/unicode/1f642.png\" title=\":simple_smile:\"></p>",
        "id": 153903171,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>&lt;name&gt;\n    &lt;use value=&quot;official&quot;/&gt;\n&lt;/name&gt;\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>says nothing about an official name.</p>",
        "id": 153903172,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503387375
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Minor thing, <code>&lt;name/&gt;</code> is illegal, you can't have blank elements.</p>",
        "id": 153903178,
        "sender_full_name": "Vadim Peretokin",
        "timestamp": 1503392994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191363\">@Vadim Peretokin</span>  Good.<br>\nWhere is that documented?</p>",
        "id": 153903335,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503451612
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's a constraint on \"element\" requiring that all elements have either a value or children.</p>",
        "id": 153903346,
        "sender_full_name": "Lloyd McKenzie",
        "timestamp": 1503460885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks. The natural place.</p>",
        "id": 153903348,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Townley-O'Neill",
        "timestamp": 1503461014
    }
]